      <abstract>Soldier from Holland, Mich., member of Co. D, 339th U.S. Infantry who served in the Allied intervention in Russia, 1918-1920, the 
"Polar Bear Expedition." Collection includes description of army life and battles of the Polar Bear campaign; also includes a reminiscence of a 
tour of Russia, 1959, with a teachers group. </abstract>
      <unitid countrycode="us" repositorycode="MiU-H" encodinganalog="099" type="call number">86705 Aa 1</unitid>
      <langmaterial>The materials are in <language encodinganalog="041" langcode="eng">English.</language></langmaterial>
      <repository>
        <corpname encodinganalog="852">
          <subarea>Bentley Historical Library</subarea> University of Michigan</corpname>
<extptr href="bhladd" show="embed" actuate="onload"/></repository>
    </did>
    <descgrp type="admin">
      <acqinfo encodinganalog="541">
        <p>The collection was donated by Mrs. Frank W. Douma, of Ottumwa, Iowa, in 1978 
(Donor no.: <num type="donor" encodinganalog="541$e">6176</num>).</p>
      </acqinfo>
      <accessrestrict encodinganalog="506">
        <p>The collection is open for research.</p>
      </accessrestrict>
      <prefercite encodinganalog="524">
        <p>item, folder title, box no., Frank W. Douma diary, Bentley Historical Library, University of Michigan</p>
      </prefercite>
    </descgrp>
    <bioghist encodinganalog="545">
      <p>Resident of <geogname normal="Holland (Mich.)">Holland, Mich.</geogname>, served as corporal, 
<corpname normal="United States. Army. Infantry, 339th. Company D.">Co. D, 339th Infantry</corpname>.</p>
    </bioghist>
    <scopecontent encodinganalog="520">
      <p>The <genreform normal="Diaries.">diary</genreform>, July 1918-July 1919, is a 
<genreform normal="Stats (copies)">photostat</genreform> of a <genreform normal="Typescripts.">typescript</genreform>, and describes 
<persname normal="Douma, Frank W., 1893-1976.">Douma's</persname> daily life and the weather as well as fighting at 
<geogname normal="Sel'tso (Russia)">Seltso</geogname>, Sept. 1918; <geogname normal="Tulgas (Russia)">Toulgas</geogname>, Nov. 1918; 
<geogname normal="Vistafka (Russia)">Vistafka</geogname>, Feb.-March 1919; and <geogname normal="Kurgomen (Russia)">Kurgomen</geogname>, 
April-May 1919. The collection also includes a <genreform normal="Reminiscences.">reminiscence</genreform> of a tour of Russia, 1959, 
with a teachers' group.</p>
    </scopecontent>
